    "This feature has been configured to download two types of data: (i) ontologies (e.g., HPO 61, GO 62, and PRO 37) and databases (i.e., a data source not represented as an ontology), which includes Linked Open Data (e.g., Comparative Toxicogenomics Database 63, UniProt Knowledgebase 64, STRING 65), data from molecular experiments (e.g., the Human Protein Atlas 66, the Genotype-Tissue Expression Project 67), and existing networks and KGs (e.g., Hetionet 19, the Monarch KG 68)."
